Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art, taken at an angle, showing figure of unidentified quadruped, schematic, pecked in outline, upright and facing right ,with exaggerated neck. To lower left of this possibly a canid standing below an arc-shaped boat. Further arc is cut off edge of image at lower left. A 10cm scale has been fitted at the bottom left of the image. Eastern Desert, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
